<TITLE> Govt moves to speed up landport activities </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 5 (bdnews24.com)A five- member committee has been formed to identify the problems related to the quick unloading of essential goods imported through different land ports. A commerce ministry statement, dated Monday, announced the names of the members of the committee, with Land Port Authority member ATM Mostafa Kamal as its convenor. The committee has been asked to submit its report, including recommendations to the commerce ministry, within the next 10 working days. An official at the ministry said that the committee began work from the day of its formation. The committee members include commerce ministry deputy secretary Bikash Chandra Saha, National Board of Revenue first secretary Noor Mohammad Mahbubul Haq. The ministry in its statement said that the committee would visit the various land ports in the country, examine the unloading of essential commodities, and see whether the ports faced common problems. It would also determine whether rational fees or taxes were being charged at the ports. The committee would be particularly concerned with detecting problems in unloading goods imported in connection with the coming Ramadan, especially perishable goods, the statement said. A decision to form the committee was taken at a meeting at the commerce ministry, with commerce adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman in the chair, on July 27. bdne
